SMNA Assignment 2 — Melbourne liveability on YouTube — Group 35

Members:
- Leon Zaritski   (s4096125)
- Raphael Urpani  (s4094828)

Repository
- GitHub: https://github.com/rurp2354/SMNA-A2
- Access details: see Access_s4094828_UG_Group_35.txt

Run order
1. python fetchYoutubeData.py      # collection (requires YOUTUBE_API_KEY env var)
2. 01_preprocessing.ipynb          # cleaning, theme buckets, edge construction
3. 02_network_analysis.ipynb       # bipartite, reply, thresholded user-user projection
4. 03_topic_modelling.ipynb        # LDA topic model (K = 6)
5. 04_extensions.ipynb             # Louvain community detection + VADER sentiment overlay

Dependencies
- Python 3.10+
- pandas
- numpy
- scikit-learn                     # used for LatentDirichletAllocation, CountVectorizer
- networkx                         # graphs, centrality, louvain_communities, modularity
- matplotlib
- seaborn
- vaderSentiment                   # REQUIRED by 04_extensions.ipynb for sentiment overlay
- google-api-python-client         # only needed if re-running fetchYoutubeData.py

Notes
- The previously hardcoded YouTube Data API key has been removed from
  youtubeClient.py. The script now reads the key from the YOUTUBE_API_KEY
  environment variable.
- A representative cleaned-data sample (< 10 MB) is included in data_sample/.
- The full reproducible pipeline is the four notebooks above, executed in order.
